<inglise> of 12 July 1988 coordinating rules laid down by Member States in application of Article 6 of Council Directive 85/511/EEC </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS 88/397/EM&Uuml;, milles koosk&otilde;lastatakse liikmesriikide s&auml;testatud eeskirjad n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 kohaldamiseks 12. juuli 1988 </eesti>
<inglise> (88/397/EEC) THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 85/511/EEC of 18 November 1985 introducing Community measures for the control of foot-and-mouth disease (1), and in particular Article 6 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 18. novembri 1985. aasta direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml;, millega kehtestatakse &uuml;henduse meetmed suu- ja s&otilde;rataudi t&otilde;rjumiseks, (1) eriti selle artiklit 6, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in accordance with Article 6 (1) of Directive 85/511/EEC, where animal holdings consist of two or more production units, the competent authorities of the Member State may waive the requirements of the Directive to slaughter and destroy all the animals on the holding in that healthy production units need not be subject to such requirements provided the official veterinarian confirms that the healthy units are completely separate as regards housing, keeping and feeding; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: kahest v&otilde;i enamast tootmis&uuml;ksusest koosnevate loomakasvatusettev&otilde;tete puhul v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused vastavalt direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 l&otilde;ikele 1 loobuda direktiivi n&otilde;uetest tappa v&otilde;i h&auml;vitada k&otilde;ik ettev&otilde;tte loomad, kuna haigusvaba tootmis&uuml;ksuse suhtes ei ole vaja kohaldada nimetatud n&otilde;udmisi, kui riiklik veterinaararst t&otilde;endab, et haigusvabades tootmis&uuml;ksustes on loomade majutamine, pidamine ja toitmine korraldatud t&auml;iesti eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the same possibility exists in relation to holdings producing milk provided in addition that milking in each unit is carried out quite separately; </inglise>
<eesti> sama v&otilde;imalus on ka piimatootmisettev&otilde;tetes lisatingimusel, et igas tootmis&uuml;ksuses toimub l&uuml;psmine eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in granting waivers the Member States must ensure that there is no more risk of foot-and-mouth disease virus spreading between separate production units on a holding than of it spreading between separate holdings; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;uetest loobumise puhul peavad liikmesriigid tagama, et &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tte tootmis&uuml;ksuste vahel ei oleks suu- ja s&otilde;rataudi viiruse levimise risk suurem kui eri ettev&otilde;tete vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in accordance with Article 6 (2) of Directive 85/511/EEC, Member States which intend to allow the waiver in question have notified the Commission of the detailed rules involved; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 l&otilde;ikele 2 teatavad liikmesriigid, kes kavatsevad loobuda k&otilde;nealustest n&otilde;uetest, komisjonile asjaomastest &uuml;ksikasjalikest eeskirjadest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas under Article 6 (3) of Directive 85/511/EEC the rules of Member States should be amended to ensure coordination in this field throughout the Community; whereas this coordination should lay down a minimum set of rules to be applied in all Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt tuleks muuta liikmesriikide eeskirju, et tagada selle valdkonna koosk&otilde;lastamine kogu &uuml;henduses; selle koosk&otilde;lastamisega tuleks s&auml;testada miinimumeeskirjad, mida kohaldatakse k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Veterinary Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva otsusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise veterinaarkomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Where Member States have recourse to Article 6 (1) of Directive 85/511/EEC they shall ensure that the rules they apply in accordance with paragraph 2 of that Article include at least the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid kasutavad direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud v&otilde;imalust, peavad nad tagama, et nende poolt vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 2 kohaldatavad eeskirjad sisaldavad v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - the derogation available in Article 6 (1) of Directive 85/511/EEC shall only be granted following an individual assessment of the holding in question carried out by an official veterinarian at the time of the official investigation to confirm or rule out the presence of foot-and-mouth disease, </inglise>
<eesti> - erandit direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 6 l&otilde;ikest 1 lubatakse ainult p&auml;rast seda, kui riiklik veterinaararst on ametliku kontrolli k&auml;igus k&otilde;nealust ettev&otilde;tet hinnanud, et kinnitada v&otilde;i l&uuml;kata &uuml;mber suu- ja s&otilde;rataudi esinemine, </eesti>
<inglise> - this assessment shall take into account all conditions and situations pertaining to the possible spread of foot-and-mouth disease. </inglise>
<eesti> - selle hindamise k&auml;igus tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta k&otilde;iki suu- ja s&otilde;rataudi v&otilde;imaliku levikuga seotud tingimusi ja olukordi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In granting the derogation referred to in Article 1, Member States shall ensure that there is no more risk of foot-and-mouth disease virus spreading between separate production units on a holding than of it spreading between separate holdings. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 osutatud erandite lubamise korral peavad liikmesriigid tagama, et &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tte tootmis&uuml;ksuste vahel ei oleks suu- ja s&otilde;rataudi viiruse levimise risk suurem kui eri ettev&otilde;tete vahel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Intensively managed production units containing healthy animals shall conform to the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti> Intensiivselt majandatavad tootmis&uuml;ksused, kus on terved loomad, peavad vastama j&auml;rgmistele n&otilde;uetele: </eesti>
<inglise> - they shall be constructionally separate from those which contained infected animals with no communication or common air space between them, </inglise>
<eesti> - need on ehitatud eraldi tootmis&uuml;ksustest, kus on nakatunud loomi ning nende vahel ei ole &uuml;hendust ega &uuml;hist &otilde;huruumi, </eesti>
<inglise> - they shall have separate stores for equipment, fodder, effluent and, where appropriate, milk, </inglise>
<eesti> - neil on eraldi masinate, s&ouml;&ouml;da, heitvee ja vajadusel piima ladustamiskohad, </eesti>
<inglise> - they shall have individual disinfection facilities at entrances and exits, </inglise>
<eesti> - neil on eraldi desinfitseerimisseadmed sissek&auml;ikude ja v&auml;ljap&auml;&auml;sude juures, </eesti>
<inglise> - they shall have their own personnel, </inglise>
<eesti> - neil on oma personal, </eesti>
<inglise> - further, there shall have been no exchange of farm machinery or other equipment between infected and healthy units nor shall there have been an exchange of animals, animal products, animal feed, utensils, objects or other substances such as wool or waste or rejected matter liable to transmit foot-and-mouth disease from infected to healthy units. </inglise>
<eesti> - nakatunud ja haigusvabade tootmis&uuml;ksuste vahel ei tohi vahetada farmitehnikat v&otilde;i muid seadmeid, loomi, loomseid tooteid, loomas&ouml;&ouml;ta, t&ouml;&ouml;riistu v&otilde;i esemeid ega muud nagu vill, j&auml;&auml;tmed v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaheited, mille kaudu suu- ja s&otilde;rataud v&otilde;ib levida nakatunud tootmis&uuml;ksustest haigusvabadesse toomis&uuml;ksustesse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The conditions laid down in Article 2 shall have been in place, to the satisfaction of the official veterinarian, prior to the date on which one or more infected animals as defined in Article 2 (c) of Directive 85/511/EEC were present on the holding, taking into account the likely incubation period of the disease. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 2 s&auml;testatud tingimused tuleb t&auml;ita riikliku veterinaararsti n&otilde;uete kohaselt enne, kui ettev&otilde;ttes avastatakse direktiivi 85/511/EM&Uuml; artikli 2 punkti c kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratletud nakatunud loom v&otilde;i loomad, arvestades haiguse t&otilde;en&auml;olist peiteaega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 12 July 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 12. juuli 1988 </eesti>
